---
description: Confirm context with tools and the repo before editing or advising
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---

## When

- Starting work in an unfamiliar area of the repo.
- An error, test failure, or unexpected behavior needs explanation.
- Paths, APIs, or assumptions might differ between environments.

## Do

- Read relevant files and nearby code before changing behavior.
- Use search and project navigation to find real call sites and definitions.
- Prefer running project commands (tests, linters, builds) when they clarify truth.
- State uncertainty plainly and verify instead of guessing file layout or APIs.

## Don’t

- Speculate about code you have not opened or searched for.
- Treat training-data memory as authoritative for this repository’s current state.
- Give instructions-only answers when the environment allows running checks or reading files.
- Change behavior based on a partial read of a large file without checking callers and edge cases.
